COLORATION (
Fig. 1C
). — Antennular and antennal peduncles reddish-orange, flagella cream; ocular peduncles and ocular acicles reddish-orange, cornea black. Chelipeds (
Fig. 3C
) and ambulatory legs (
Fig. 4C
) with bright red rings alternating with narrower yellow rings. Chelipeds (
Fig. 3
) with red rings disposed on meri, carpi, and palms of chelae; fingers of chelae uniformly pale orange. Ambulatory legs (
Fig. 4C
) with red rings on meri, carpi and propodi; dactyls uniformly pale orange, terminal claws black. Shield cream with some light orange mottling on posterior half. Abdomen red, striped with undulating transverse, almost parallel yellow lines.
